    <h2 {...{
      "id": "i-fsx-for-windows"
    }}>{`I. FSx for Windows`}</h2>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">{`EFS is a shared POSIX compliant system for Linux. FSx is a fully managed Windows file system share drive.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Supports SMB protocol and Windows NTFS. Also AD and LDAP, ACLs.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Storage of up to 64 TB per file system.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Built on top of SSD, scale up to 10s of GB/s, `}<Quote mdxType="Quote">{`millions of IOPS`}</Quote>{`, 100s of PBs of data.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">
        <Quote mdxType="Quote">Can be accessed from your on-prem infrastructure.</Quote>
      </li>
      <li parentName="ol">
        <Quote mdxType="Quote">Can be configured to be multi-AZ.</Quote>
      </li>
      <li parentName="ol">
        <Quote mdxType="Quote">Data is backed up daily to S3.</Quote>
      </li>
      <li parentName="ol">
        <Quote mdxType="Quote">To migrate your existing file data into FSx, use Windows Robust File Copy (RoboCopy) to copy your files directly to FSx.</Quote>
      </li>
    </ol>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "ii-fsx-for-lustre"
    }}>{`II. FSx for Lustre`}</h2>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Lustre = Linux + Cluster `}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`It is a type of parallel distributed file system for large scale computing.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Used in ML and HPC, quant finance, EDA`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Scales up to 100s of GB/s, `}<Quote mdxType="Quote">{`millions of IOPS`}</Quote>{`, <1ms latency`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Can be mounted on-prem servers using DirectConnect.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`You can use FSx as your "hot" storage and S3 for "cold" storage.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Seamless integration with S3`}
        <ol parentName="li">
          <li parentName="ol">
            <Quote mdxType="Quote">Can read S3 as a file system (through FSx)</Quote>
          </li>
          <li parentName="ol">{`Can write the output of the computations back to S3 (through FSx)`}</li>
        </ol>
      </li>
    </ol>
    <p><img alt={"FSx"} src={require("!url-loader?limit=10000&name=assets/images/[name]-[hash].[ext]&fallback=file-loader!./../src/media/fsx.png").default} /></p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "iii-fsx-tips"
    }}>{`III. FSx Tips`}</h2>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Auto replication within the AZ it resides in.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Offers single AZ and multi-AZ deployment options for your Windows file-based workloads.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Uses the Volume Shadow Copy Service (VSS) to automatically take highly durable, file-system consistent daily backups to S3.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Default backup retention period is 7 days.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Supports identity based auth over SMB for Microsoft AD.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">
        <Quote mdxType="Quote">Automatically encrypts data at-rest using KMS and in-transit using SMB kerberos session keys.</Quote>
      </li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`PCI and HIPAA compliant.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Billed hourly based on configured storage capacity and throughput capacity.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Billed hourly for your backup storage (GB-month).`}</li>
    </ol>
    </MDXLayout>;
}

